-- MOVES-Standard Chartered Bank Bahrain names Shaikha Tareef CFO
-- 
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 09:54AM EDT
-- None



Oct 1 (Reuters) - Standard Chartered Bank Bahrain, a branch of Standard Chartered Plc <STAN.L>, said it appointed Shaikha Tareef as chief financial officer.

Tareef is the first Bahraini woman CFO in the bank's history, Standard Chartered Bahrain said in a statement. She will be responsible for implementation of the bank's financial strategy and controls and handle cost management, the bank said.